16/10/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UN police reported on Wednesday (15 October) the arrest of three people who allegedly tried to smuggle 36kg of heroin into Kosovo from Albania.
The street value of the drugs was 1.5m euros.
A police spokesman said the heroin was found in a vehicle carrying Austrian registration plates.
Two of those arrested are Albanian nationals;
the third is an ethnic Albanian from Kosovo.
(AFP - 15/10/03)
